<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="240" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,799,1329]" pageId="3" pageNumber="240">
Cuvier (1817) referred to all the generic groups cited in his work by 
<emphasis box="[910,1112,799,825]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="240">nomina vernacula</emphasis>
. For already existing genera, he also specified the Latin name in parentheses together with an abbreviation of the author’s name [e.g. Les Éponges (
<taxonomicName box="[161,253,871,897]" class="Demospongiae" family="Spongiidae" genus="Spongia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Dictyoceratida" pageId="3" pageNumber="240" phylum="Porifera" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[161,253,871,897]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="240">Spongia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
L.), Les Millépores (
<taxonomicName authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1758" box="[499,611,871,897]" class="Hydrozoa" family="Milleporidae" genus="Millepora" kingdom="Animalia" order="Anthoathecata" pageId="3" pageNumber="240" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[499,611,871,897]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="240">Millepora</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
L.), Les Renilles (
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lamarck" authorityYear="1816" box="[828,909,871,897]" class="Anthozoa" family="Renillidae" genus="Renilla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Pennatulacea" pageId="3" pageNumber="240" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[828,909,871,897]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="240">Renilla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
L.), Les Pennatules (
<taxonomicName authority="Cuv." authorityName="Cuv." box="[1155,1336,870,897]" class="Anthozoa" family="Pennatulidae" genus="Pennatula" kingdom="Animalia" order="Pennatulacea" pageId="3" pageNumber="240" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1155,1270,871,897]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="240">Pennatula</emphasis>
Cuv.
</taxonomicName>
)], but he did not devise scientific names for his newly proposed taxa (e.g. Les Pavonaires Cuv., Les Scirpéaires Cuv., Les Ombellulaires Cuv.). According to Article 12.3 of ICZN4, a vernacular name cannot serve as an “indication” to make available a name that lacks a description or definition. For this reason, the name “Les Pavonaires” proposed by Cuvier (1817) is unavailable. In fact, all of the new genus-level names proposed by Cuvier (1817) first became available later, in works using their Latin equivalents (e.g. 
<taxonomicName authority="Gray, 1870" authorityName="Gray" authorityYear="1870" box="[809,1059,1051,1077]" class="Anthozoa" family="Umbellulidae" genus="Umbellula" kingdom="Animalia" order="Pennatulacea" pageId="3" pageNumber="240" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[809,927,1051,1077]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="240">Umbellula</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Gray, J. E." box="[935,1059,1051,1077]" pageId="3" pageNumber="240" refId="ref5285" refString="Gray, J. E. (1870) Catalogue of the sea-pens or Pennatulariidae in the collection of the British Museum. British Museum, London, 40 pp. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 11307" type="book" year="1870">Gray, 1870</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
for Les Ombellulaires Cuv.).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,799,1329]" pageId="3" pageNumber="240">
<bibRefCitation author="Oken, L." box="[199,343,1087,1113]" pageId="3" pageNumber="240" pagination="144 - 148" refId="ref5853" refString="Oken, L. (1817) Cuviers und Okens Zoologien neben einander gestellt. Isis oder Encyclopadische Zeitung von Oken, 1 (VIII, 144 - 148), 1145 - 1186." type="journal article" year="1817">Oken (1817)</bibRefCitation>
published a study comparing Cuvier’s classification to his own, listing all genera of the Animal Kingdom and mentioning the name 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kolliker. This" authorityYear="1870" box="[551,669,1124,1149]" class="Anthozoa" family="Halipteridae" genus="Pavonaria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Pennatulacea" pageId="3" pageNumber="240" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[551,669,1124,1149]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="240">Pavonaria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
within the group “ 
<taxonomicName box="[875,994,1123,1149]" class="Anthozoa" family="Pennatulidae" genus="Pennatula" kingdom="Animalia" order="Pennatulacea" pageId="3" pageNumber="240" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="genus">Pennatula</taxonomicName>
”. For reasons mentioned in above in the Introduction, this was a 
<emphasis box="[419,583,1159,1185]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="240">nomem nudum</emphasis>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Schweigger, A. F." box="[637,850,1159,1185]" pageId="3" pageNumber="240" refId="ref5933" refString="Schweigger, A. F. (1819) Beobachtungen auf naturhistorischen Reisen. Anatomisch-Physiologische Untersuchungen uber Corallen. Reimer, Berlin, 188 pp. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 14416" type="book" year="1819">Schweigger (1819)</bibRefCitation>
was the first to make the name 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kolliker. This" authorityYear="1870" box="[1203,1321,1160,1185]" class="Anthozoa" family="Halipteridae" genus="Pavonaria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Pennatulacea" pageId="3" pageNumber="240" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1203,1321,1160,1185]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="240">Pavonaria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
available. Although several studies in the 19th century (Cuvier, 1836; 
<bibRefCitation author="Richiardi, S." box="[847,1027,1195,1221]" pageId="3" pageNumber="240" pagination="1 - 150" refId="ref5888" refString="Richiardi, S. (1869) Monografia della famiglia dei Pennatularii. Archivio per la zoologia l'anatomia e la fisiologia, Series 2, 1, 1 - 150. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 9116" type="journal article" year="1869">Richiardi, 1869</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Gray, J. E." box="[1042,1171,1195,1221]" pageId="3" pageNumber="240" refId="ref5285" refString="Gray, J. E. (1870) Catalogue of the sea-pens or Pennatulariidae in the collection of the British Museum. British Museum, London, 40 pp. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 11307" type="book" year="1870">Gray, 1870</bibRefCitation>
, and even 
<bibRefCitation author="Schweigger, A. F." pageId="3" pageNumber="240" refId="ref5933" refString="Schweigger, A. F. (1819) Beobachtungen auf naturhistorischen Reisen. Anatomisch-Physiologische Untersuchungen uber Corallen. Reimer, Berlin, 188 pp. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 14416" type="book" year="1819">Schweigger, 1819</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Schweigger, A. F." box="[224,281,1231,1257]" pageId="3" pageNumber="240" refId="ref5973" refString="Schweigger, A. F. (1820) Handbuch der Naturgeschichte der skelettlosen ungegliederten Thiere. Dyk'schen Buchhandlung, Leipzig, 776 pp. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 59209" type="book" year="1820">1820</bibRefCitation>
) attributed the authorship of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kolliker. This" authorityYear="1870" box="[623,741,1232,1257]" class="Anthozoa" family="Halipteridae" genus="Pavonaria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Pennatulacea" pageId="3" pageNumber="240" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[623,741,1232,1257]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="240">Pavonaria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to Cuvier, and publications in the 20th century attributed it to 
<bibRefCitation author="Schweigger, A. F." box="[182,397,1267,1293]" pageId="3" pageNumber="240" refId="ref5973" refString="Schweigger, A. F. (1820) Handbuch der Naturgeschichte der skelettlosen ungegliederten Thiere. Dyk'schen Buchhandlung, Leipzig, 776 pp. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 59209" type="book" year="1820">Schweigger (1820)</bibRefCitation>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Kukenthal, W." box="[413,606,1267,1294]" pageId="3" pageNumber="240" refId="ref5564" refString="Kukenthal, W. (1915) Pennatularia. In: Das Tierreich. Vol. 43. Verlag von R. Friedlander, Berlin, pp. 1 - 132." type="book" year="1915">Kükenthal, 1915</bibRefCitation>
; Deichmann, 1936, 
<bibRefCitation author="Williams, G. C." box="[836,1012,1267,1294]" pageId="3" pageNumber="240" pagination="93 - 140" refId="ref6276" refString="Williams, G. C. (1995) Living genera of sea pens (Coelenterata: Octocorallia: Pennatulacea): Illustrated key and synopses. Zoological Journal of the Linnean Society, 113, 93 - 140. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1096 - 3642.1995. tb 00929. x" type="journal article" year="1995">Williams, 1995</bibRefCitation>
), the correct citation for this taxon is 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,489,1303,1329]" pageId="3" pageNumber="240">
<taxonomicName authority="Schweigger, 1819" authorityName="Schweigger" authorityYear="1819" box="[151,484,1303,1329]" class="Anthozoa" family="Halipteridae" genus="Pavonaria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Pennatulacea" pageId="3" pageNumber="240" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="genus">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,271,1303,1329]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="240">Pavonaria</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Schweigger, A. F." box="[278,484,1303,1329]" pageId="3" pageNumber="240" refId="ref5933" refString="Schweigger, A. F. (1819) Beobachtungen auf naturhistorischen Reisen. Anatomisch-Physiologische Untersuchungen uber Corallen. Reimer, Berlin, 188 pp. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 14416" type="book" year="1819">Schweigger, 1819</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
